cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on the vulnerability of deep neural networks in image recognition tasks, specifically face verification and landmark detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also proposes an algorithm that leverages disentangled semantic factors, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). The paper also discusses the security aspect of DNNs, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper applies the proposed algorithm to street-view images, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
